724831f-a.title: Manhattan: Worth Street - Baxter Street
724831f-a.text:
Worth Street, at the S.W. corner of Baxter Street, showing a
statue of Christopher Columbus at this location, as viewed southwest-
ward towards the Municipal Building and across the low rear wing of
the new U.5. Court House.
About 1936
Gift of Michael Wishengrad, A.R.P.S.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE.
724831f-a.folder: Worth Street & Baxter Street, Manhattan, NY

716594f-a.title: Manhattan: Baxter Street - Worth Street
716594f-a.text:
(1)
23 to 3 Baxter Street (right), east side, south from Worth Street, to
Park Row. Also shown (left) is Worth Street, south side, east from
Baxter Street to Chatham Square. Also shown is a general view of the
neighboring area, south from the State Building, at the N.W. corner of
Worth and Baxter Streets, with the Brooklyn (right) and Manhattan (left)
Bridges in the distant background.
March 27, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
A portion of the same, excluding the view of Worth Street. Also shown
(right foreground) are two quadrilaterally shaped parks on the west side of
the street, in rear of the New York County Court House.
March 27, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
